My fiancÃ© does product shots for a local plant shop in the area. She will have dozens of plants to shoot that result in hundreds of photos.

Part of the job is organizing and uploading them to google photos. This means she has been renaming hundreds of files individually. ðŸ˜­  

The system they have down is: `{PLANT_NAME}{DETAIL?}{POT_SIZE}_{number}`. So for any given plant it will have several 'product' shots and several 'detail' shots taken for it.

A simple script but going to save hours of data entry!


